If P2>0 and we short, we win if the box widens further into T (T‚àíP2 > 0)?
Careful: a ‚Äúcarry-in‚Äù trade is riding the pre-move into T, not fading it.

Short on P2>0: profit if the box at T is even wider than at P2 (T > P2).

Long on P2<0: profit if the box at T is even tighter than at P2 (T < P2).
We subtract an all-in round-trip cost TC_BP to reflect execution costs.

Summaries you‚Äôll show.

Overall: N, Hit%, Avg/Med PnL (bp), Total (bp), Sharpe.

By bucket: same stats per tenor bucket.
(You can also add histograms/cum-PnL plots if you like.)

üß† Why we ‚Äúdon‚Äôt enter every day‚Äù

This strategy is event-driven: a trade only exists when there‚Äôs an auction for a given bond line.

For each auction we may enter at P2 (or P1) and exit at T. On all other days there‚Äôs no trade, so the backtest naturally has sparse entries (one per qualifying auction), not daily positions.

üîß What to tweak quickly

Baseline: change BASELINE_REL to -1 for a ‚Äúday-before‚Äù definition.

Signal choice: use "P1" instead of "P2" (or test both).

Gating: switch from Q_THRESHOLD to {K_BP = 2.0} for an absolute bp cutoff.

Costs: stress TC_BP (e.g., 0.8 ‚Üí 2.0 bp).

Window: change YEAR_WINDOW_DAYS if your ‚Äúlast year‚Äù should be trading-days not calendar days.

